## Performance Notes
- MobileNetV2 inference on CPU: ~40–80ms per image (acceptable for mobile)
- Batch size 32 is optimal for most GPUs; reduce to 16 if OOM errors occur
- TOP_K = 3 predictions is the default; Flutter displays all 3

## Phase 3 — Flutter Integration (upcoming)
- Flutter app will POST to /predict as multipart/form-data with field name "file"
- API base URL will be stored in Flutter as a constant (not hardcoded per-call)
- Flutter expects top_predictions[0] as primary result, [1] and [2] as alternatives
- example_picture field may be a URL or local asset path — Flutter handles both

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- DO NOT use @app.on_event("startup") — use lifespan instead (deprecated in FastAPI)
- DO NOT call model.predict() outside a try/except
- DO NOT return Python exceptions directly — wrap in HTTPException
- DO NOT resize images with PIL's default NEAREST — always use Image.LANCZOS
- DO NOT forget to convert PIL image to RGB before prediction (PNG may be RGBA)
- DO NOT hardcode class names — always read from class_indices.json
- DO NOT change TOP_K without checking Flutter rendering handles the new count
